      • postIssue

        @NotNull
public Response postIssue​(String summary,
                          String description,
                          boolean hidden,
                          File... files)
                   throws IOException
        Creates new issue in YouTrack for MPS projects.
        This method require call of login(jetbrains.mps.ide.blame.perform.Query) with valid or anonymous credentials first.
        Parameters:
        summary - title of the issue
        description - description of issue (system info, build info, steps to reproduce, exception message and stack traces)
        hidden - determine if issue will be visible only to creator and mps-developers group
        files - list of files to be attached to the issue
        Returns:
        response with created issue id if response succeeded
        Throws:
        IOException - can be thrown by HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpMethod)

      • setIssueField

        public Response setIssueField​(@NotNull
                              String issueId,
                              @NotNull
                              String field,
                              @NotNull
                              String value)
                       throws IOException

        Sets new value to specified field of YouTrack issue with provided ID.
        This method require call of login(jetbrains.mps.ide.blame.perform.Query) with valid or anonymous credentials first.

        ATTENTION: old value of field, if it was already set, will be overridden.
        If you need to update filed value and preserve old one, use updateIssueField(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String)

        Parameters:
        issueId - YouTrack issue with this id will be updated
        field - of issue to change (as shown in web)
        value - value which will be set to issue field
        Returns:
        server response to update query
        Throws:
        IOException - can be thrown by HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpMethod)

      • updateIssueField

        public Response updateIssueField​(@NotNull
                                 String issueId,
                                 @NotNull
                                 String field,
                                 @NotNull
                                 String value)
                          throws IOException

        Adds new value to specified field of YouTrack issue with provided ID.
        This method require call of login(jetbrains.mps.ide.blame.perform.Query) with valid or anonymous credentials first.

        ATTENTION: new value of field, will be added to current value.
        If you need to override old value, use setIssueField(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String)
        Parameters:
        issueId - YouTrack issue with this id will be updated
        field - of issue to update (as shown in web)
        value - value which will added to field
        Returns:
        server response to update query
        Throws:
        IOException - can be thrown by HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpMethod)

      • listVersions

        @TestOnly
@NotNull
public Response listVersions()
                      throws IOException
        Requests for list of versions. This method require call of login(jetbrains.mps.ide.blame.perform.Query) with valid credentials first. To retrieve list, user must be part of mps-developers group
        Returns:
        server response for list of versions request
        Throws:
        IOException - can be thrown by HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpMethod)

      • countUnresolvedIssues

        public Response countUnresolvedIssues​(Map<String,​Integer> users2counts)
                               throws IOException
        https://www.jetbrains.com/help/youtrack/standalone/Get-Number-of-Issues-for-Several-Queries.html
        Parameters:
        users2counts - map of Youtrack login and placeholder value that would get populated on successful execution of the command.
        Returns:
        modifies map values, reporting number of issues for a user. Note, null value is left in case API didn't answer with number of issues (gave -1). You may want to issue request few times to get answer (for whatever reason, Youtrack not necessarily answers at the first request, even with 'sync')
        Throws:
        IOException - in case of communication error
